body:
`__filename` is a node.js variable that gives the filename of the current file. If you place this code in a nested file only this file will be added to the buildDependencies and not the top-level file. So changes to the top-level file won't be detected.

`__filename` must be placed in the top-level webpack config.

In your case it probably make sense to pass it from the top-level config:

``` diff
 // webpack.config.js
 const fullPath = "\/home\/valentas\/Projects\/webpack-5-persistent-cache";
 
 module.exports = require(`${fullPath}\/app\/config\/webpack.config.js`)({
+    "config": __filename,
     "entry": {
         "style-97d6614bde722784c18a56c668d3e0090ddd8302": `${fullPath}\/src\/index.js`,
     },
```

``` diff
 // app/config/webpack.config.js
        config.cache = {
            type: 'filesystem',
            cacheDirectory: `${cacheDirectory}/webpack`,
            buildDependencies: {
                config: [
-                   __filename,
+                   options.config,
                ],
            },
        };
```
